						<summary>

						<p>On the same pillar in the same Museum No. 90.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record, engraved on the fourth face of the same pillar [Museum No. 90], seems to be a different record but damaged very much.</p>						

						<p>Dējarasa, Tribhuvanamalla and Sōmēśvara described as <hi rend="italic">narēśvara,</hi> are mentioned in the record. Besides, there is a mention of Ganga, Kaḷinga and Siṁhaḷa kings. Since, the beginning is broken and lost and the end is completely damaged the purport of the record is not clear. It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
